The paper discusses the societal value alignment problem in the context of artificial intelligence, which is a core topic in the field of AI (cs.AI). The use of game theory to model conflicts and equilibria suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the potential unintended consequences of AI systems, which falls under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of stochastic models suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of stochastic systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits and potential inequalities that may arise from the adoption of AI systems, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
